LE-LE AND HER HUSBAND, CHANG KAI
OUR FAMILY

92
00:07:52,166 --> 00:07:53,750
LE-LE TURNED ONE

93
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:56,250
FIRST TIME SEEING CHERRY BLOSSOMS

94
00:07:56,333 --> 00:08:00,875
MY DAUGHTER AT TEN YEARS OLD

95
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:06,000
TANG AND I
TANG IS GONE

96
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,791
I'm Cheng Kuang-chi.

97
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,458
I can take care of myself.

98
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:35,250
I'M CHENG KUANG-CHI
MY DAUGHTER CHENG LE-LE

99
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,833
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF

100
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:08,458
I told you to use a wheelchair.
Why do you have to act tough?

101
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:09,791
No wheelchair.

102
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:11,708
Why? This is dangerous…

103
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:13,416
Hey, look!

104
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,375
See?

105
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,708
- Cheng Kuang-chi, sit down.
- Help me.

106
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,250
Fine…

107
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,333
I'll sit down.

108
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:22,583
Sit. You're too old for this.

109
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:24,125
You just hurt your foot.

110
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:26,458
- Lower your voice.
- Why don't you listen?

111
00:09:26,541 --> 00:09:28,500
- Okay. Sit down.
- It's a hospital…

112
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:37,791
Lift your legs up.

113
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:44,000
Lift it up. Be careful.

114
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:48,250
I had to give it a try.

115
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:51,125
- Put these on the foot pedals.
- Okay.

116
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,333
Keep it steady.

117
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:53,791
Sure, no problem.

118
00:09:53,875 --> 00:09:56,500
Your seatbelt came off.
Let me buckle you up.

119
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:00,291
Come on, sit still.

120
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:02,666
Why are you holding your shoe?

121
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,666
Here, I'll put it on.

122
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:07,583
Okay, sit still.

123
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:09,291
All right.

124
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:43,166
CHANG KAI:
YOU AWAKE?

125
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:46,083
LE-LE:
YES

126
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:54,000
CHANG KAI:
IS YOUR DAD OKAY?

127
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:06,625
LE-LE: OKAY MY ASS!
HE'S PRETTY TRENDY THOUGH

128
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:13,666
HE HAS DELIRIUM NOW.
IS HE TRYING TO WEAR ME OUT?

129
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:22,250
LE-LE:
HE'S OKAY. HOW ARE YOU?

130
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:43,833
CHANG KAI: THIS MIGHT SEEM ABRUPT
BUT AFTER LUNAR NEW YEAR

131
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:48,416
WOULD YOU CONSIDER
MOVING TO SINGAPORE WITH ME?

132
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,416
Watch out, there's a ramp.

133
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:18,458
- Okay, good. Steady.
- Hold on tight.

134
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:19,625
Yes…

135
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:12,416
- Hello.
- Is your foot okay now?

136
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,083
- Much better.
- Really?

137
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:15,458
Yeah, thank you.

138
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:29,875
The worst part of divorce
is changing your emergency contact

139
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:32,125
from your husband to your parents.

140
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:36,375
Actually, my dad
was recently diagnosed with dementia.

141
00:13:36,458 --> 00:13:39,708
He's not the best person
to handle any emergencies now.

142
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:43,416
If one day something happens to me
and I end up in the hospital,

143
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,500
"Mr. Cheng,
your daughter's in the hospital."

144
00:13:45,583 --> 00:13:46,791
"Please get here now."

145
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:48,625
And my dad would say,

146
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:51,916
"You have the wrong person.
Who's Mr. Cheng?" Then he hangs up.

147
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,583
Then I'd go, "Dad, wait!"

148
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,916
"Answer the phone! My life's at stake!"

149
00:13:57,458 --> 00:14:00,250
- Where's Mark?
- He left. He seemed pissed off.

150
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:05,458
Hey, that breakup sex bit was dope.
I loved it.

151
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:07,583
Awesome.

152
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:11,916
- I gotta take this.
- Sure, go ahead.

153
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,375
- Hello?
<i>- Where's my underwear?</i>

154
00:14:14,458 --> 00:14:16,875
- In the dresser.
- I can't find it.

155
00:14:16,958 --> 00:14:19,041
In the dresser in the bathroom.

156
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:21,791
I told you not to move my stuff, didn't I?

157
00:14:21,875 --> 00:14:24,625
<i>My stuff is where it should be.</i>

158
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:27,291
<i>Yeah? You said</i>
<i>you'd be an obedient daughter.</i>

159
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:28,625
<i>You gotta be obedient.</i>

160
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:30,916
Obey me, not yourself.

161
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:32,625
Don't wear it today.

162
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:33,833
No way.

163
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,750
<i>Or wear the old one inside out.</i>

164
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,583
<i>What time do you finish work?</i>

165
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:39,791
It's fine if you don't wear it for a day.

166
00:14:39,875 --> 00:14:41,500
It'll feel airy without it.

167
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,750
Hey, don't you have to work?
You've got so much free time.

168
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:17,666
Hey, is your foot okay now?

169
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,708
Yeah, my foot's fine.

170
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,833
Time to get rid of the crutches.

171
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,875
It's only a little better.

172
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:26,125
Don't just wander off.

173
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:27,541
Yeah.

174
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:33,166
What?

175
00:15:35,291 --> 00:15:38,166
Are you my mom or am I your dad?

176
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,333
Looks like you're fully recovered.

177
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:42,833
Yeah.

178
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,166
Hey.

179
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:46,583
This blazer looks nice, right?

180
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:48,583
I bought it at Sincere.

181
00:15:50,541 --> 00:15:52,583
Sincere closed down years ago.

182
00:15:52,666 --> 00:15:55,125
No, I got this at Sincere.

183
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:01,125
Dad, where are you going?
I'll go with you.

184
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,541
No, it's okay.

185
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:05,208
I'm going to the corner store
to borrow… I…

186
00:16:12,083 --> 00:16:13,625
It looks good, right?

187
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,333
It looks good.

188
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:20,708
I bought it at Sincere.

189
00:16:26,708 --> 00:16:29,333
Dad, what's for New Year's Eve dinner
this year?

190
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:32,000
- It's New Year again?
- Yep.

191
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:35,458
Oh, right.

192
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:39,416
I was going to the corner store to buy
red paper for writing Spring Couplets.

193
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,500
No Spring Couplets this year.

194
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:45,458
No way, we have to write them
for the New Year.

195
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:48,958
Just like how it won't be the New Year
without New Year's Eve dinner.

196
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:50,625
All right.

197
00:16:50,708 --> 00:16:52,333
Here, hold on.

198
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,708
- Taking pills again?
- Yes.

199
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,041
- So many?
- Yeah.

200
00:16:57,125 --> 00:16:59,708
Take them now, or there'll be more.
Here, come on.

201
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:02,875
Here.

202
00:17:06,958 --> 00:17:08,333
That's a good boy.

203
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:15,666
Hey, it looks good, right?

204
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:20,125
You bought it at Sincere.

205
00:17:50,416 --> 00:17:54,208
<i>It's called acute delirium,</i>
<i>also known as the elderly's silent killer.</i>

206
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:59,000
<i>Its onset increases the risk of dementia</i>
<i>and disability, and even death.</i>

207
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:01,666
<i>It's a sudden brain confusion,</i>
<i>so it comes on quickly.</i>

208
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,791
<i>The condition fluctuates a lot.</i>

209
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:06,541
<i>Sometimes good,</i>
<i>sometimes bad, going back and forth.</i>

210
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:10,166
<i>That's why close observation,</i>
<i>companionship, and care are important…</i>

211
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:28,791
<i>Hey, Le-le.</i>

212
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:31,791
<i>Why don't you come home</i>
<i>for New Year's Eve dinner?</i>

213
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:34,958
I've told you.
I'm working the night shift.

214
00:18:35,041 --> 00:18:38,166
Oh boy, who works during the New Year's?

215
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:41,083
They pay me double for the night shift.

216
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:43,500
I'm on my own after the separation.

217
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,041
<i>All right, that's it for now.</i>

218
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:49,666
<i>I have to head out now.</i>

219
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,875
Hey, Le-le.

220
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:51,916
Tell me,

221
00:18:52,458 --> 00:18:54,916
what's your wish for the New Year?

222
00:19:00,083 --> 00:19:01,041
Happiness.

223
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:06,958
- Oh.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

224
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:09,750
<i>- Bye.</i>
- Okay, bye-bye.

225
00:19:20,375 --> 00:19:21,833
Wishing you good wealth!

226
00:19:22,541 --> 00:19:24,958
Those in the front,
please come to the center.

227
00:19:25,041 --> 00:19:28,541
- Pray to the Goddess Mazu for blessings.
- Everyone gets one.

228
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,625
Wishing you good wealth!

229
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:34,041
- Wishing you good wealth!
- Stop pushing.

230
00:19:35,208 --> 00:19:36,666
Wishing you good wealth!

231
00:19:40,291 --> 00:19:42,791
Why can't I just sleep in

232
00:19:42,875 --> 00:19:44,958
on the first day of the New Year?

233
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:48,291
Happy New Year.

234
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:52,375
Go back to sleep.

235
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:06,750
<i>Don't forget…</i>

236
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:07,666
HAPPINESS

237
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,583
<i>…stick the "fortune" upside down,</i>

238
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,333
<i>and fortune will arrive.</i>

239
00:20:11,416 --> 00:20:15,791
<i>Stick the "happiness" upside down too,</i>
<i>and happiness will arrive.</i>

240
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,041
Come get your pork!

241
00:20:58,125 --> 00:20:59,250
Good deals here!

242
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:01,291
Get your ribs!

243
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,666
Come buy some meat!

244
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:06,083
Come get your meat and ribs!

245
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:07,333
Ma'am.

246
00:21:07,416 --> 00:21:09,791
- What can I get for you?
- I want some pork belly.

247
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:12,791
Will you braise it or steam it?

248
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:17,416
I'll give you a good deal.
How much do you want? Or do you want ribs?

249
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:22,208
Well, it's okay. I'll come back later.

250
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,666
Okay.

251
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:16,750
KEEP THE DOCTOR AWAY

252
