<i>The kitchen staff never stopped.</i>
<i>A thousand people were waiting for dinner.</i>

253
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,750
<i>The chef said for the New Year's dishes,</i>

254
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,750
<i>they've prepared 250 kg of lobster</i>

255
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:28,750
<i>and 80 kg of fish maw.</i>

256
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:30,708
<i>The last day of the shopping…</i>

257
00:23:10,416 --> 00:23:12,416
Turn the Tide Beef Noodles.

258
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:14,333
Prosperous and Vibrant Tomato Noodles.

259
00:23:14,416 --> 00:23:16,208
Booming Success Wine Chicken.

260
00:23:16,291 --> 00:23:18,708
Everything Goes Well Soybean Noodles.

261
00:23:19,625 --> 00:23:20,666
This one…

262
00:23:21,958 --> 00:23:23,250
The original flavor.

263
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:25,125
Mine's omelet rice.

264
00:23:25,208 --> 00:23:26,791
You've been cooking all afternoon.

265
00:23:27,666 --> 00:23:29,125
This is nice. Good job.

266
00:23:30,625 --> 00:23:33,208
I thought you didn't like instant noodles?

267
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:35,875
Why do you still cook it all the time?

268
00:23:35,958 --> 00:23:38,375
This is all I can cook.

269
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:41,750
Okay, pick one that you like.

270
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:42,750
Okay.

271
00:23:44,083 --> 00:23:45,333
Well…

272
00:23:45,416 --> 00:23:46,916
I'll pick this one.

273
00:23:48,166 --> 00:23:50,541
You picked the original flavor? Come on.

274
00:23:50,625 --> 00:23:53,458
No, the original flavor is good.
It tastes great.

275
00:23:57,541 --> 00:23:59,291
You used to add lots of stuff.

276
00:24:00,541 --> 00:24:02,666
I wanted you to have more nutrition.

277
00:24:12,208 --> 00:24:13,583
You've done a good job.

278
00:24:15,375 --> 00:24:16,791
- Really?
- Yeah.

279
00:24:19,583 --> 00:24:22,041
Mommy's cooking smells so good!

280
00:24:22,125 --> 00:24:23,500
Kids, dinner's ready.

281
00:24:23,583 --> 00:24:24,541
Get ready for dinner.

282
00:24:24,625 --> 00:24:25,625
Put away your toys.

283
00:24:25,708 --> 00:24:27,791
- Shaw, help Anne put the toys away.
- Put them…

284
00:24:27,875 --> 00:24:29,125
- Why are you crying?
- Sit.

285
00:24:29,208 --> 00:24:30,625
That's okay.

286
00:24:31,875 --> 00:24:33,500
Anne, no.

287
00:24:33,583 --> 00:24:35,625
- Mommy's got you.
- Mommy's here.

288
00:24:36,125 --> 00:24:37,458
Come here, son.

289
00:24:37,541 --> 00:24:39,708
Oh, sweetie.

290
00:24:41,291 --> 00:24:43,375
Okay, what were we playing earlier?

291
00:24:43,458 --> 00:24:44,583
The car slide, remember?

292
00:24:44,666 --> 00:24:45,583
Your hands.

293
00:24:46,125 --> 00:24:47,458
Your hands. Stay here.

294
00:24:47,541 --> 00:24:49,125
Come on.

295
00:24:49,208 --> 00:24:50,958
- Someone needs the elevator.
- Good.

296
00:24:51,041 --> 00:24:52,875
Dad, Mom.

297
00:24:53,416 --> 00:24:55,000
Happy New Year.

298
00:24:55,083 --> 00:24:57,500
- Are you having New Year's Eve dinner?
- Spoon…

299
00:24:58,791 --> 00:25:00,958
Let me take a picture
for Grandma and Grandpa.

300
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,000
Look at me.

301
00:25:34,041 --> 00:25:36,958
Hey, let's go on a trip
after the New Year.

302
00:25:45,375 --> 00:25:47,875
Why do they play the same game every year?

303
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:51,041
- Yeah, they don't change it up.
- Yeah.

304
00:25:53,375 --> 00:25:55,625
But what is his name?

305
00:25:55,708 --> 00:25:58,250
He's not bad. He's doing all right.

306
00:25:58,333 --> 00:25:59,375
- Yeah.
- Right?

307
00:25:59,458 --> 00:26:02,250
He's one of the funnier ones.

308
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:03,500
Right.

309
00:26:14,083 --> 00:26:15,416
Happy New Year.

310
00:26:18,791 --> 00:26:19,750
Hold on.

311
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,375
- Is it for me?
- Yes.

312
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:26,166
All the best for the year.

313
00:26:27,541 --> 00:26:29,583
Be happy every day.

314
00:26:29,666 --> 00:26:30,583
Oh, dear.

315
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,500
Thank you.

316
00:26:34,416 --> 00:26:35,333
This is great.

317
00:26:35,416 --> 00:26:37,208
It's a bit light, though.

318
00:26:37,291 --> 00:26:38,750
Don't say that, okay?

319
00:26:42,958 --> 00:26:45,833
<i>This feels like </i>The Truman Show.

320
00:26:46,333 --> 00:26:48,333
What's more terrifying is

321
00:26:48,916 --> 00:26:50,375
you're in this world.

322
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,791
Nobody makes it out alive.

323
00:26:57,416 --> 00:26:58,291
Your foot.

324
00:27:00,791 --> 00:27:02,041
- Your foot.
- What?

325
00:27:02,125 --> 00:27:03,041
Your foot!

326
00:27:06,125 --> 00:27:07,125
<i>And the elderly…</i>

327
00:27:07,208 --> 00:27:08,375
Mr. Cheng.

328
00:27:08,458 --> 00:27:09,625
<i>…stay inside 24/7.</i>

329
00:27:09,708 --> 00:27:10,666
Take your pills.

330
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:12,166
<i>Why does this sound</i>

331
00:27:12,250 --> 00:27:13,791
so scary?

332
00:27:13,875 --> 00:27:16,375
- Because this place really exists.
- Morning, Le-le.

333
00:27:16,458 --> 00:27:19,916
Do you know there's a place
in the Netherlands called De Hogeweyk?

334
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,625
- It's a nursing home.
- She's…

335
00:27:21,708 --> 00:27:25,500
<i>And it's for seniors with severe dementia.</i>

336
00:27:25,583 --> 00:27:28,541
<i>This sounds cruel.</i>

337
00:27:30,458 --> 00:27:33,916
<i>Because they have no idea</i>
<i>what's going on around them.</i>

338
00:27:34,416 --> 00:27:37,541
<i>And they're watched and monitored</i>
<i>around the clock.</i>

339
00:27:38,208 --> 00:27:41,750
<i>They are surrounded by medical staff.</i>
<i>But they don't know that.</i>

340
00:27:42,250 --> 00:27:44,791
<i>They are looked after and cared for daily.</i>

341
00:27:44,875 --> 00:27:47,166
<i>It's actually a pretty good life.</i>

342
00:27:47,250 --> 00:27:48,166
Especially…

343
00:27:49,583 --> 00:27:51,333
When they shop…

344
00:27:52,041 --> 00:27:52,875
Hello.

345
00:27:52,958 --> 00:27:55,250
<i>Especially when they shop,</i>
<i>they don't need to pay.</i>

346
00:27:57,375 --> 00:27:58,583
- Separate receipts?
- Yes.

347
00:27:58,666 --> 00:27:59,583
Pay with cash?

348
00:27:59,666 --> 00:28:01,416
<i>- The cashier will tell them…</i>
- Yes.

349
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:03,166
<i>"Hey, you don't have to pay."</i>

350
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:04,666
<i>"You paid last time."</i>

351
00:28:07,833 --> 00:28:10,583
Isn't that just like <i>The Truman Show</i>?

352
00:28:24,875 --> 00:28:27,250
NO GIG FOR YOU TOMORROW NIGHT

353
00:28:41,291 --> 00:28:43,000
I'm coming.

354
00:28:43,083 --> 00:28:45,041
- Hi.
- Hello.

355
00:28:45,125 --> 00:28:46,916
- Hey, handsome.
- Hi.

356
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,666
How come you're home?

357
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:50,000
- Chia-yun?
- I'm Su-fei.

358
00:28:50,083 --> 00:28:51,791
- Shoes off.
- I'm Su-fei.

359
00:28:51,875 --> 00:28:53,500
- Keep your shoes on.
- Yeah?

360
00:28:53,583 --> 00:28:55,208
- That's fine.
- You're here.

361
00:28:55,291 --> 00:28:56,416
This is Anne.

362
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:59,041
- Hello.
- Anne, this is Mr. Cheng.

363
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,583
- For me?
- Le-le, which cup?

364
00:29:02,666 --> 00:29:04,208
- For you.
- You're so generous.

365
00:29:04,291 --> 00:29:05,291
Here…

366
00:29:06,125 --> 00:29:07,500
Wait, I'll tidy up.

367
00:29:07,583 --> 00:29:08,416
Want some?

368
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:12,583
Anything to drink?

369
00:29:12,666 --> 00:29:15,083
- Hey, your dad is good with kids.
- Kaoliang.

370
00:29:15,166 --> 00:29:17,500
- Did you see this giraffe?
- He's a kid too.

371
00:29:17,583 --> 00:29:18,541
- Giraffe.
- Hey.

372
00:29:19,125 --> 00:29:20,875
I got a coupon two days ago.

373
00:29:20,958 --> 00:29:22,708
A duplex with a great view.

374
00:29:22,791 --> 00:29:25,125
It has an outdoor hot spring,
and it's 40% off.

375
00:29:25,208 --> 00:29:27,333
How about we go there for our trip?

376
00:29:27,416 --> 00:29:28,625
Can I bring my two kids?

377
00:29:28,708 --> 00:29:30,625
Can I bring my old man?

378
00:29:30,708 --> 00:29:32,000
What? Bathe with them?

379
00:29:32,083 --> 00:29:33,625
That's ridiculous.

380
00:29:34,125 --> 00:29:37,125
It's hard to talk to
married and divorced women.

381
00:29:37,208 --> 00:29:39,208
No wonder I only hang out
with the singles.

382
00:29:39,291 --> 00:29:42,666
I might be able to make it
if it's a day trip.

383
00:29:42,750 --> 00:29:45,083
I'll see if my mother-in-law
can babysit my kids.

384
00:29:45,166 --> 00:29:46,458
Me too.

385
00:29:47,041 --> 00:29:48,791
Yeah, like I'm twisting your arms.

386
00:29:49,583 --> 00:29:50,916
You want that cup?

387
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:54,083
I book the restaurants.
You're often skipping Period Club.

388
00:29:54,166 --> 00:29:56,958
We talked about a trip.
You can't even commit.

389
00:29:57,875 --> 00:29:58,791
Never mind.

390
00:29:58,875 --> 00:30:00,916
- Come on. This is for you.
- No.

391
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,000
Are you on your period?

392
00:30:03,416 --> 00:30:04,250
Watermelon.

393
00:30:04,333 --> 00:30:05,291
No.

394
00:30:05,875 --> 00:30:10,000
Sorry, we've been busy
and haven't had time to hang out.

395
00:30:11,458 --> 00:30:13,916
Do you find us boring now?

396
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,916
How can life always be interesting?

397
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,208
Exactly.

398
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:21,083
You both have family stuff
to talk about. Do I?

399
00:30:23,083 --> 00:30:27,291
Hey, why was the glass of water sad?

400
00:30:27,791 --> 00:30:31,541
Because it felt empty.

401
00:30:31,625 --> 00:30:32,541
Am I right?

402
00:30:33,041 --> 00:30:35,500
Right? So empty.

403
00:30:35,583 --> 00:30:36,541
Look, I have two.

404
00:30:38,750 --> 00:30:40,208
Hey, look at that.

405
00:30:40,291 --> 00:30:43,458
- Weren't we going to drink Kaoliang?
- Yeah, I'll open it for you.

406
00:30:44,208 --> 00:30:45,125
Hold on.

407
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:48,291
I want some too.

408
00:30:53,916 --> 00:30:57,083
Be careful with the bike.
Don't let it fall on you again.

409
00:30:57,166 --> 00:30:58,208
Okay.

410
00:30:59,208 --> 00:31:02,375
I've made all your meals
and put them in the fridge.

411
00:31:02,875 --> 00:31:05,333
Just heat them up if you're hungry.

412
00:31:05,416 --> 00:31:06,250
Okay.

413
00:31:06,333 --> 00:31:07,625
Don't forget your pills.

414
00:31:07,708 --> 00:31:08,916
I've divided them.

415
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,375
They are in the pill case.

416
00:31:12,125 --> 00:31:13,875
And I've written down

417
00:31:14,416 --> 00:31:15,833
your emergency contacts.

418
00:31:15,916 --> 00:31:18,833
I've put them up on the door,
the fridge, and the bathroom.

419
00:31:18,916 --> 00:31:20,500
I've spoken to Mrs. Liu.

420
00:31:20,583 --> 00:31:21,958
If anything happens,

421
00:31:22,041 --> 00:31:24,375
just contact us or her, okay?

422
00:31:27,541 --> 00:31:28,500
Dad.

423
00:31:29,875 --> 00:31:30,833
Dad.

424
00:31:31,791 --> 00:31:33,916
You'll be back tomorrow, right?

425
00:31:38,166 --> 00:31:39,041
Yes.

426
00:31:39,666 --> 00:31:41,375
I'll be back tomorrow.

427
00:31:41,458 --> 00:31:42,708
Cheng Le-le!

428
00:31:43,458 --> 00:31:45,166
Your driver's here.

429
00:31:45,250 --> 00:31:47,166
Remember to eat and take your pills.

430
00:31:47,250 --> 00:31:50,375
I'll be back soon.
Emergency contact info is here.

431
00:31:51,416 --> 00:31:53,041
Bye. I'll bring treats for you.

432
00:31:53,125 --> 00:31:57,625
Cheng Le-le, hurry up! I've been waiting.

433
00:31:58,958 --> 00:31:59,833
Hurry up!

434
00:31:59,916 --> 00:32:03,333
- I've been waiting for so long.
- I'm coming.

435
00:32:03,416 --> 00:32:05,000
- Hurry up!
- Okay.

436
00:32:06,791 --> 00:32:07,833
Mr. Cheng, we're off.

437
00:32:07,916 --> 00:32:09,416
We're off. Bye.

438
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:11,583
Be good and stay home. I'll be back soon.

439
00:32:11,666 --> 00:32:13,583
I'll take care of your daughter.

440
00:32:36,958 --> 00:32:39,125
- Isn't it pretty?
- It's so nice!

441
00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:42,000
I told you we should come here.

442
00:32:42,083 --> 00:32:43,416
Oh my God!

443
00:32:43,958 --> 00:32:45,875
Gosh! This bed…

444
00:32:46,625 --> 00:32:48,000
- Wait.
- You haven't showered.

445
00:32:48,083 --> 00:32:49,541
Seriously?

446
00:32:49,625 --> 00:32:51,416
What did you say to Chang Kai?

447
00:32:53,208 --> 00:32:54,625
She hasn't replied.

448
00:32:55,208 --> 00:32:57,166
I can't deal with that right now.

449
00:32:57,750 --> 00:32:59,250
Yeah, I get it.

450
00:32:59,333 --> 00:33:00,875
Yeah? You get it?

451
00:33:01,500 --> 00:33:03,291
Well, you don't get it.

452
00:33:03,375 --> 00:33:04,916
Right, I don't.

453
00:33:05,625 --> 00:33:07,291
How can a happy single lady

454
00:33:07,375 --> 00:33:10,708
understand the miseries
of married women like us?

455
00:33:13,666 --> 00:33:15,416
I have my own problems, okay?

456
00:33:16,375 --> 00:33:17,583
- Like what?
- Such as?

457
00:33:18,625 --> 00:33:20,666
My collar bones don't really show.

458
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:22,125
Mine never did.

459
00:33:25,375 --> 00:33:27,875
You can't compare pain.

460
00:33:27,958 --> 00:33:29,291
Of course you can.

461
00:33:29,375 --> 00:33:31,916
All pain comes from comparison, okay?

462
00:33:32,791 --> 00:33:34,041
The pain of childbirth,

463
00:33:34,666 --> 00:33:35,916
the pain of breastfeeding,

464
00:33:36,416 --> 00:33:38,916
the pain of spending
the New Year with my mom-in-law.

465
00:33:39,666 --> 00:33:41,625
You don't know how lucky you are.

466
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:44,041
Like I said, you'll never get it.

467
00:33:46,041 --> 00:33:48,250
What time is it?
Should I video call my son soon?

468
00:33:48,333 --> 00:33:49,166
No.

469
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:50,791
I should call my dad soon too.

470
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:52,250
No.

471
00:33:52,333 --> 00:33:54,166
Hey, we just got here three hours ago.

472
00:33:54,250 --> 00:33:55,583
My skin's all wrinkled.

473
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:57,000
It's only been five minutes.

474
00:33:57,500 --> 00:33:59,083
Another 20 seconds then.

475
00:34:06,916 --> 00:34:08,125
Handsome.

476
00:34:08,208 --> 00:34:10,083
Do you miss me? Do you miss Mommy?

477
00:34:14,125 --> 00:34:15,833
What did you eat today?

478
00:34:15,916 --> 00:34:17,125
<i>Daddy gave me a popsicle.</i>

479
00:34:17,208 --> 00:34:18,291
<i>It was so yummy.</i>

480
00:34:19,041 --> 00:34:22,916
You had a popsicle?
It was so sweet and tasty, right?

481
00:34:23,625 --> 00:34:24,666
But it's cold today.

482
00:34:24,750 --> 00:34:27,125
Isn't your dad worried
you'll get a sore throat?

483
00:34:27,791 --> 00:34:30,125
And what happens for seven hours
after you eat sugar?

484
00:34:30,708 --> 00:34:32,416
You won't grow tall.

485
00:34:33,875 --> 00:34:35,666
Shaw, excuse me.

486
00:34:35,750 --> 00:34:37,541
I'm borrowing your mom today.

487
00:34:37,625 --> 00:34:39,333
Get some rest and sleep early.

488
00:34:39,416 --> 00:34:41,583
Honey, don't keep scrolling
in front of the kids.

489
00:34:44,541 --> 00:34:46,541
You're a control freak.

490
00:34:46,625 --> 00:34:48,666
All the men run away from you.

491
00:34:48,750 --> 00:34:49,875
No, I'm not!

492
00:34:49,958 --> 00:34:52,583
It's like this now.
He won't even come home when he's older.

493
00:34:53,583 --> 00:34:54,833
He will.

494
00:34:54,916 --> 00:34:56,250
But with a girlfriend.

495
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,125
I really can't recall
the last time I used a facial mask.

496
00:35:01,208 --> 00:35:04,625
Oh well, it's never too late
to start skincare.

497
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:08,375
It feels great
to leave my kids and husband behind.

498
00:35:08,458 --> 00:35:11,166
I've actually
thought about how great it'd be

499
00:35:11,958 --> 00:35:15,375
to leave my dad behind
and go to Singapore with Chang Kai.

500
00:35:16,583 --> 00:35:17,833
Okay, I know.

501
00:35:18,333 --> 00:35:20,083
It's wrong to think this way.

502
00:35:22,708 --> 00:35:25,958
But if I had siblings,
I wouldn't be burdened like this.

503
00:35:26,041 --> 00:35:27,625
At least not as much.

504
00:35:29,958 --> 00:35:31,250
I'm really exhausted.

505
00:35:36,208 --> 00:35:38,875
Let's not talk about
these depressing things anymore.

506
00:35:38,958 --> 00:35:39,875
- Okay?
- Yeah.

507
00:35:40,458 --> 00:35:41,416
- Okay.
- Cheers.

508
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:44,041
I'll toast with tea.
I'm taking Chinese medicine.

509
00:35:44,541 --> 00:35:45,541
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

510
00:35:45,625 --> 00:35:46,541
Cheers.

511
00:36:53,916 --> 00:36:54,833
Hello?

512
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:49,708
Okay. Thanks.

513
00:37:50,333 --> 00:37:51,916
Cheng Kuang-chi, age 80, male.

514
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:52,916
Roll the bed in.

515
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,500
